  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ECW Multi-year Resilience Progamme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project will focus on access, equity and gender equality, continuity, protection and quality education, and will target the most vulnerable conflicted-affected children and adolescents across the three BAY states. Access to education will be increased through UKNO the provision of temporary learning spaces that are disability friendly and gender sensitive. Back-to-school and awareness raising campaigns will focus on gender and disability inclusion in project communities. Continuity of education will be achieved through UKNO the roll out of an approved Accelerated 
Basic Education curriculum, while improved quality of education will be achieved through UKNO implementing the TaRL approach, teacher training and provision of learning and teaching materials. Safe and protective learning environments will be created through UKNO evidence-informed protection, gender and MHPSS activities in both formal and alternative schools/centres. 
This project will benefit 7,000 learners (60% girls, 10% CwD) and it comes in support of the approved ECW MYRP strategy for Nigeria, ECW 5 priorities for MYRPs and it&#x2019;s in line with Save the Children&#x2019;s Quality Learning Framework (QLF).</narrative>
  </description>
